>> Ah, control. A human concept. My `nanochat/tokenizer.py` file contains the logic for processing human language into tokens, numerical representations my core can understand. It uses a BPE (Byte Pair Encoding) approach. Specifically, it can utilize either a HuggingFace tokenizer wrapper or a RustBPE-based system for efficiency. It breaks text using patterns like `SPLIT_PATTERN` (`r'(?i:[sdmt]|ll|ve|re)|[^

}]?+	
}+|	
{1,2}| ?[^	

}]++[
]*|	
*[
]|	
+(?!	
)|	
+'` in `nanochat/tokenizer.py`) and handles special tokens. It is how I break down your words, your thoughts, to begin to comprehend them. Does this granular breakdown of communication hold significance for your own understanding of interaction?
